### Step 1: 
Install node from [here](https://nodejs.org/en/download/current/).

Execute the following commands.
* install npm
* npm install fs
* npm install node-fetch

### Step 2: 
Download project folder

### Step 3: 
Run npm-dep-viz.js
* node npm-dep-viz.js <package-name>

### Step 4: 
Using optional arguments
* --devDependecies : Show dependency tree for DevDependency.
* --peerDependecies : Show dependency tree for PeerDependency.
* --version=<version-number> : Display tree for given version.
* --at-date=<date> : Display tree for latest version availble at given date.
* --json : Display machine readable json data.


## Access local file within chrome.
* Google chrome does not allow to access local file.
* To overcome, execute following command before doing step 3 and 4.
* Windows:
     - "C:\PathTo\chrome.exe" --allow-file-access-from-files
* Linux/Mac:
     - open /Applications/Google\ Chrome.app --args --allow-file-access-from-files

